	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The NROM boards allegedly don't have the CHR write enable lines wired up. (A modded NROM board does, but not even UNIF has a structure to represent wirewrap modifications that don't correspond to the behavior of a commercial game's PCB.) The most primitive official board allowing CHR writing is BNROM; the second most primitive is the much more common UNROM/UOROM (which adds a 74*32 quad-OR gate to create a fixed section). With a PRG ROM of 16 KB (or less), behavior of B*ROM and U*ROM is identical.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
